<font color="#FF0000">TRAVELING WALL</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 30  0:07:44 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
After all this time, I still have not made it to Washington to visit the Wall. I'm not sure if I have been ready. However, i have been to the Traveling Wall a number of times. The most significant was at the Ohio State Fair several years ago. I was there late at night with my son and nephew after a hot day at the fair. I walked the Wall with the boys and tried to explain it. Then they went off and I sat down on a bench near the middle sort of staring into infinity - remembering. I guess I had the &quot;look&quot;. When we started to leave. An older woman came up and stopped us and said I wasn't leaving without a hug which she proceeded to give me. Her son was on the Wall. We talked for awhile. I can't really describe how I felt. There was a lightness and relief and .... It was a good feeling and part of coming home.<br>
Since then, my son has gone to Washington on a school trip and left some of my writings about Nam at the Wall. He hasn't really talked about it.<br>

<p><code>-- bgcalm68@fuse.net  (Bill Garbett) </code><p>


